eZ publish installation guide
-----------------------------

Dependencies:

 - MySQL ( www.mysql.org )
 - PHP ( www.php.net )
 - ImageMagick ( www.imagemagick.org )
 - Apache ( www.apache.org )
 - libxml ( www.xmlsoft.org )

PHP install:

 - Unpack your php-4.0.x.tar.gz package:
   # tar zxvf php-4.0.x.tar.gz

 - Howto configure php
  # cd php-4.0.x
  # ./configure --with-xml --enable-trans-sid --with-mysql --with-magic-quotes --with-apxs --with-dom

 - Compile and install the PHP package
  # make
  # make install

Apache config:

 - Rewrite and php modules needs to be active to use publish.

 - A httpd.conf virtalhost example will looks something like this: (change the publish.org to your own domain)

   # User site
   <VirtualHost publish.org>
    <Directory /home/publish/www>
          Options FollowSymLinks Indexes ExecCGI
          AllowOverride None

          RewriteEngine On
          RewriteRule     !\.(gif|css|jpg) /home/publish/www/index.php
    </Directory>

    ServerAdmin your_mail@domain.no
    DocumentRoot /home/publish
    ServerName publish.org
    ServerAlias www.publish.org
  </VirtualHost>

  # Admin site
  <VirtualHost admin.publish.org>
    <Directory /home/publish/www/admin>
          Options FollowSymLinks Indexes ExecCGI
          AllowOverride None
    </Directory>

    RewriteEngine On
    RewriteRule     !\.(gif|css|jpg) /home/publish/www/admin/index.php

    ServerAdmin your_mail@domain.no
    DocumentRoot /home/publish/admin/www
    ServerName admin.publish.org
    ServerAlias admin.publish.org
  </VirtualHost>

Install publish:

 - Make a database, call it publish ( or whatever you like )
   # mysqladmin -uroot -p create database publish

 - Add a publish user in MySQL, to add a user you can use the MySQL client.
   mysql>grant all on publish.* to publish@localhost identified by "secret";

 - Dump all the sql data from sql/publish.sql into your database
   # mysql -uroot -p publish < sql/publish.sql

 - Put all the publish files in your apache documentroot
   # cd /path/to/apache/documentroot/
   # tar zxvf /path/to/publish-1.0.tar.gz

 - Edit site.ini
   Add all the modules you need, and set the username and password.

 - Run modfix, this is important. This script will create symbolic links needed and set permissions.
  # ./modfix.sh

 - Start konqueror and have fun!
  # konqueror http://yoursite.com

 - NOTE!
   The default admin username and password will be admin/trade. Remember to change the password!!
